<p class="backstory">For eons there was war between the angels and demons. Some of the angels recognized the hopelessness and so they turned away from the war to start a new life on 
Erda. They created beings today known as humans. Though, these beings were no longer immortal or had healing abilities like their parents. The creatures of hell were a threat to 
humankind and so the angels wanted to protect their creation and some returned to the war.<br><br>

A few centuries passed, humans colonized Erda and some of the demons now also had the idea of leaving the perpetual war. Their arrival on Erda did not stay unnoticed and so, many of 
them have been pushed back into hell. Very few though remained on this new realm and so every once in a while there has been a bond between angel and demon. Though, they and their 
offspring have been hunted down as these mixed creatures can barely control which side is showing. They are known to wreak havoc and are therefore a threat to humans.<br><br><br>

Artiya'il was one of those mixed children. Her father, an oh so angelic noble man, met her mother and their lives became intertwined. Sadly, soon after they were caught and 
incarcerated. Artiya'il was born in a damp and dark cell between moldy straw and rat droppings. Two years later, her father fled and left her and her mother behind. And so he left 
his scythe.<br><br>

Another few years passed and one day Artiya'ils mother managed to smuggle her out along with her father's scythe, before getting murdered by the fed up guards. Artiya'il had to 
stay hidden most of her life, as she would have been chased and killed. Artiya'il began to hate everything and everyone and sought vengeance.<br><br>

A life in hiding made her a good observer and she has seen the many terrible faces of humanity. Many years have passed and the religious faith of mankind began to wane. Epidemics 
and diseases started to ravage and soon after, ruptures started to appear everywhere. The end was nigh. Demons emerged from the cracks and slaughtered everything and everyone in 
sight. Among them was Artiya'il, ready for her long awaited revenge.</p>

